ProtoTheorem:
. "If $P=\{a_{n_i}\}_1^\infty$ and $Q= \{a_{m_j}\}_1^\infty$ 
   are respectively the subsequences of all positive and 
   negative terms in a conditionally convergent series $\sum 
   a_n$ then \begin{equation} \sum_{i=1}^\infty a_{n_i}=\infty 
   \quad and\quad \sum_{j=1}^\infty a_{m_j}=-\infty. 
   \end{equation}"
